on through GooglersGive.

00:01:04.353 --> 00:01:08.070
As a bit more background on
Bev, by discipline, Beverly

00:01:08.070 --> 00:01:10.420
is an entrepreneurial
behavioral scientist

00:01:10.420 --> 00:01:12.720
and has made her career in
the field of social change

00:01:12.720 --> 00:01:15.220
marketing over
the past 30 years.

00:01:15.220 --> 00:01:17.600
She has a background in
advertising and communications

00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:20.560
and has an extensive career
in marketing, especially

00:01:20.560 --> 00:01:24.410
in the field of social change,
working in private, nonprofit,

00:01:24.410 --> 00:01:27.220
and public sectors on
issues from drug prevention

00:01:27.220 --> 00:01:31.860
and smoking prevention to
gender equity and education.

00:01:31.860 --> 00:01:35.440
About the book, "Rippling"
is described as a blueprint

00:01:35.440 --> 00:01:38.060
for visionary thinking about how
to tackle the world's biggest

00:01:38.060 --> 00:01:41.110
social and environmental
challenges.

00:01:41.110 --> 00:01:44.310
She draws on examples
of empathy, innovation,

00:01:44.310 --> 00:01:47.630
creativity, passion,
and persistence

00:01:47.630 --> 00:01:50.280
to make real change in the
world and pulls case studies

00:01:50.280 --> 00:01:54.910
from Ashoka Fellows to
exemplify these characteristics.

00:01:54.910 --> 00:01:57.510
"Rippling" has won
two big awards,

00:01:57.510 --> 00:02:00.970
including the 2013 Nautilus
Award and the 2013 "Inc.

00:02:00.970 --> 00:02:03.767
Magazine"-sponsored Axiom
Business Book Award.

